Troubleshoot Your Bot

Bots are an integrated product—they include Bot features, input from Chat and Messaging channels, and they work together with Apex and Flows. A great way to get started is to learn how to use the Event Logs to troubleshoot.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots: 
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

NOTE In orgs created in Summer ’23 and later, Salesforce automatically enables enhanced Omni-Channel routing. Enhanced Omni-Channel routing doesn’t support standard bots or channels.

If the issue is with the bot, check the bot’s event logs.
From the Bot Builder menu, click Performance. Then select the Event Logs tab.
The log displays chat session information for the last seven days. If a session has errors, details about the error are in the Errors column.

To drill into a session, click the session ID. Each session includes events, which map to dialogs. If there’s an error with an event, click next to the event for more information.
If the error is less than 7 days old, a notification shows on the dialog related to the error. To view the event logs related to the dialog error, click the link in the notification.

To see additional details in event logs, enable Log Conversations on the Einstein Bots setup page. If your bot is missing required permissions, add the permissions to the sfdc.chatbot.service.permset permission set.
If your bot is heavily customized with Apex, review the Debug Logs.

title: Troubleshooting Einstein Bots in Service Cloud
